<li>
    <!-- Button trigger modal -->
    <button type="button" id="simulationBtn" class="btn btn-primary" data-toggle="modal" data-target="#sceneModal">
        Simulation
    </button>

  
    <!-- Modal -->
    <div class="modal fade" id="sceneModal" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="sceneModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
        <div class="modal-dialog" role="document">
            <div class="modal-content">
            <div class="modal-header">
                <h5 class="modal-title" id="sceneModalLabel">Weather simulation</h5>
                <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
                <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                </button>
            </div>
            <div class="modal-body">
                Weather simulation is a new feature we are trying to fully add. We have only two scenes: Sunny and Rainy and working for more.
                In future, It will reflect today's weather for the main city.
                It is to know, simulations only run on computers (not smartphones) and can slow interactions with the site depending on computer performance. 
                You can simply refresh the page to make a simulation disappear.
            </div>
            <div class="modal-footer">
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal" onclick="offScene()">Close</button>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="initScene('rain')">Rain demo!</button>
                <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary" onclick="initScene('sun')">Sun demo!</button>
            </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</li>